(PS: Someday I'm going back to FV and killing EVERY SINGLE ONE of those damn spiders just for revenge, hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p>Balthemal says: "Save me, Jboots, save me!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wolf04468>wolf04468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/02 2:22:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  forget oasis </span><hr size=1> Try LOIO get near the mill (ask someone to guide you... very helpfull or get a map) and once you get there you can pull the Sabertooth Tigresses (not tigers) Sabertooth cats are a little low but may still give exp. Also you can solo Sarnak FLunkies (not conuscripts) goblin battlemasters(not aggresors) and maybe some skellies i went here with my 16 warrior and downtime was little with my bind wound got a level a day of off and on playing and it seemed pretty good =) good if you hate oasis (ahem like i did) or anyother little zone <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lehtotinkertank>LehtoTinkertank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/30/02 11:37:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left 